<subSubSection pageId="524" pageNumber="525" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="524" pageNumber="525">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName LSID="A3C432E5-C2A1-53FC-BBF9-B7667CA45757" authority="Casey, 1918" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Monoferonia)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="524" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Monoferonia">Monoferonia Casey, 1918</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="524" pageNumber="525" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="524" pageNumber="525">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Monoferonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="524" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Monoferonia</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 322, 363. Type species: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="524" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mancus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="524" pageNumber="525">Evarthrus mancus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1853 by original designation. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="524" pageNumber="525">monos</emphasis>
(one) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="524" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="524" pageNumber="525">Feronia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="524" pageNumber="525">q.v</emphasis>
.], probably alluding to the presence of a single discal setigerous puncture on the third elytral interval in these 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="524" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="524" pageNumber="525">Feronia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="524" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="524" pageNumber="525">Pterostichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) species [feminine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="524" pageNumber="525" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="524" pageNumber="525">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="524" pageNumber="525">Four species in the Appalachian region of eastern North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="524" pageNumber="525" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="524" pageNumber="525">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="524" pageNumber="525">Darlington (1932) reviewed the species and provided a key for their identification.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
